(9781400033423, 'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/81bPIejP-JL._AC_UY327_FMwebp_QL65_.jpg', 'One, No One and One Hundred Thousand', 'English', 'identity, self-perception, society', 'Riverhead Books', 371, 'One, No One and One Hundred Thousand is a novel by Italian writer Luigi Pirandello, originally published in 1926. The book explores the themes of identity, self-perception, and the complex relationship between individuals and society. Through the protagonists quest to understand his own identity and how others perceive him, the novel delves into the intricacies of human existence and the multifaceted nature of truth.');
